    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1972-05-31T09:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1972-05-31T09:30:00-05:00" n="180"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d180">
                <head>180. Diary Entry by the Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff (<persName
                        corresp="#p_MTH1">Moorer</persName>)<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d180fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss target="#t_RG1"
                            >RG</gloss> 218, Records of the Chairman, <persName corresp="#p_MTH1"
                            >Moorer</persName> Diary, July 1970–July 1974.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1972-05-31T10:30:00-04:00">May 31, 1972, 10:30 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">Met with—<gloss target="#t_LTG1">LTG</gloss>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ZM1">Zais</persName> and <gloss target="#t_LTG1"
                            >LTG</gloss>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KRT2">Knowles</persName>—in office</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Told them to prepare a memo to <gloss target="#t_SecDef1">SecDef</gloss>
                    summarizing the operation in North Vietnam listing the <gloss target="#t_BDA1"
                        >BDA</gloss>, show the bridges that have been destroyed, the rolling stock,
                    the thermal power plants, show where the mining has occured, transformer struck,
                    etc. Current plans are to provide for continuation of strikes against the
                    railroad and roads. Also have plan to seal off the <gloss target="#t_WBLC1"
                        >WBLC</gloss> routes from China.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_ACW1">Abe</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d180fn2">General <persName corresp="#p_ACW1"
                            >Abrams</persName>.</note> has stated his intent is, following the
                    stabilization of the land battle, to concentrate against the storage areas in
                        <gloss target="#t_RP1">RP</gloss> 1 and 2.<note n="3" xml:id="d180fn3">Route
                        Packages 1 and 2 were the target zones in North Vietnam closest to the
                            <gloss target="#t_DMZ1">DMZ</gloss>.</note> Use B–52s that are
                    available.</p>
                <p>We have three months of good weather ahead of us, have the air units in place,
                    probably will be the last opportunity to force the <gloss target="#t_NVN1"
                        >NVN</gloss> to a reasonable negotiation. We must take advantage of the
                    situation to inflict the maximum damage aimed to force <gloss target="#t_NVN1"
                        >NVN</gloss> to negotiation posture. Move forward with a very aggressive
                    bombing campaign, which will not only interdict <gloss target="#t_NVN1"
                        >NVN</gloss> efforts to bring in supplies, but also destroy power supplies
                    in Hanoi and Haiphong areas.</p>
            </div>
